"https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/lsr/#PQR/202408180130/202408180130"}, "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-121.59, 45.65]}}, {"id": "14", "type": "Feature", "properties": {"valid": "2024-08-18T21:52:00Z", "type": "D", "magnitude": null, "city": "3 WNW Odell", "county": "Hood River", "state": "OR", "source": "NWS Employee", "remark": "Few downed trees, unknown time.", "wfo": "PQR", "typetext": "TSTM WND DMG", "lon0": -121.59, "lat0": 45.65, "events": "", "tdq": false, "warned": false, "leadtime": null, "lsrtype": "SV", "link": "https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/lsr/#PQR/202408182152/202408182152"}, "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-121.59, 45.65]}}, {"id": "15", "type": "Feature", "properties": {"valid": "2024-09-07T02:30:00Z", "type": "D", "magnitude": null, "city": "4 ENE Blue River", "county": "Lane", "state": "OR", "source": "NWS Employee", "remark": "Tree fell down onto power lines in the evening. Gusts up to 30+ mph, approximated using peak winds from nearby IRAWS.", "wfo": "PQR", "typetext": "TSTM WND DMG", "lon0": -122.26, "lat0": 44.16, "events": "", "tdq": false, "warned": false, "leadtime": null, "lsrtype": "SV", "link": "https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/lsr/#PQR/202409070230/202409070230"}, "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-122.26, 44.16]}}, {"id": "16", "type": "Feature", "properties": {"valid": "2024-10-28T21:23:00Z", "type": "W", "magnitude": null, "city": "3 W Longview", "county": "Cowlitz", "state": "WA", "source": "Public", "remark": "Corrects previous funnel cloud report from 3 W Longview. Upon review of further photos and videos, this was a short-lived waterspout over the Columbia River near the Lewis and Clark bridge at Longview. Indicated on radar and media reported.", "wfo": "PQR", "typetext": "WATERSPOUT", "lon0": -122.99, "lat0": 46.13, "events": "", "tdq": false, "warned": false, "leadtime": null, "lsrtype": "MA", "link": "https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/lsr/#PQR/202410282123/202410282123"}, "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-122.99, 46.13]}}, {"id": "17", "type": "Feature", "properties": {"valid": "2024-10-31T15:56:00Z", "type": "T", "magnitude": null, "city": "South Beach", "county": "Lincoln", "state": "OR", "source": "Public", "remark": "EF-0 tornado with estimated max wind of 80 mph. The tornado briefly touched down in South Beach, OR at the Oregon State University Ship Operations facility. About 20 square feet of concrete shingles were torn off one building, with various items in the path weighing up to 1100 pounds blown over or pushed aside. Touchdown was at the southwest corner of the damaged building, with the tornado moving northeast. Width is estimated at 10 yards, expanding to up to 20 yards once it passed over water. Estimated path length is around .16 miles based on video evidence and damage.", "wfo": "PQR", "typetext": "TORNADO", "lon0": -124.05, "lat0": 44.62, "events": "", "tdq": false, "warned": false, "leadtime": null, "lsrtype": "TO", "link": "https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/lsr/#PQR/202410311556/202410311556"}, "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-124.05, 44.62]}}, {"id": "18", "type": "Feature", "properties": {"valid": "2024-11-12T05:24:00Z", "type": "T", "magnitude": null, "city": "Rockaway Beach", "county": "Tillamook", "state": "OR", "source": "Trained Spotter", "remark": "*** 1 INJ *** EF-0 tornado with estimated winds of 85 mph. The tornado briefly touched down in Rockaway Beach, OR. It occurred around 9:24 PM 11/11/24 and lasted one to two minutes or so according to the spotter that reported it. KRTX radar imagery depicted a fairly strong velocity couplet over Rockaway Beach. This likely formed as a waterspout then made landfall, though the path was not continuous. There have been multiple reports of damage to fences, roof shingles, and a window and dirt/debris being tossed around. Upon further investigation, more security camera video footage was received from the Neah-Kah-Nie School district showing distinct rotation of a tornado moving through a parking lot where several items were thrown or moved including portions of a baseball dug-out, porta-potty, and several dumpsters. A garage on the premises had its roof blown off and the garage doors blown in. One minor injury was reported. The maximum width of the the tornado is estimated at 150 yards and an estimated path length of 0.25 miles based on damage reports.", "wfo": "PQR", "typetext": "TORNADO", "lon0": -123.94, "lat0": 45.61, "events": "", "tdq": false, "warned": false, "leadtime": null, "lsrtype": "TO", "link": "https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/lsr/#PQR/202411120524/202411120524"}, "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-123.94, 45.61]}}, {"id": "19", "type": "Feature", "properties": {"valid": "2024-11-12T05:24:00Z", "type": "T", "magnitude": null, "city": "Rockaway Beach", "county": "Tillamook", "state": "OR", "source": "Trained Spotter", "remark": "A trained spotter in Rockaway Beach, Oregon called and reported a tornado near the beach in the town of Rockaway Beach. It occurred around 9:24 PM 11/11/24 and lasted a minute or so according to the spotter. At that exact time, KRTX radar imagery depicted a fairly strong velocity couplet over Rockaway Beach. There have been multiple reports of damage to fences, roof shingles, a window and dirt/debris being tossed around. The Rockaway Beach Community Facebook page has a few pictures of damage, including a video showing a downed fence and another video showing a small downed tree. As more reports come in, we may need to perform a storm damage survey in-person to access the damage and determine is this can be considered a confirmed tornado. FOR NOW, THIS TORNADO REPORT IS PRELIMINARY AND THE LOCATION AND TIMING IS APPROXIMATE. Updates will be provided as needed.", "wfo": "PQR", "typetext": "TORNADO", "lon0": -123.94, "lat0": 45.62, "events": "", "tdq": false, "warned": false, "leadtime": null, "lsrtype": "TO", "link": "https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/lsr/#PQR/202411120524/202411120524"}, "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-123.94, 45.62]}}, {"id": "20", "type": "Feature", "properties": {"valid": "2024-11-20T23:23:00Z", "type": "W", "magnitude": null, "city": "10 WSW Klipsan Beach", "county": "PZZ251", "state": "WA", "source": "Trained Spotter", "remark": "A well-defined waterspout formed off the Long Beach peninsula, and was observed from 316 to 323 pm.", "wfo": "PQR", "typetext": "WATERSPOUT", "lon0": -124.25, "lat0": 46.43, "events": "", "tdq": false, "warned": false, "leadtime": null, "lsrtype": "MA", "link": "https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/lsr/#PQR/202411202323/202411202323"}, "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-124.25, 46.43]}}, {"id": "21", "type": "Feature", "properties": {"valid": "2024-11-21T00:12:00Z", "type": "W", "magnitude": null, "city": "3 S Cape Shoalwater", "county": "PZZ251", "state": "WA", "source": "Public", "remark": "Video provided from a member of the public. Video is available on our social media pages.", "wfo": "PQR", "typetext": "WATERSPOUT", "lon0": -124.09, "lat0": 46.69, "events": "", "tdq": false, "warned": false, "leadtime": null, "lsrtype": "MA", "link": "https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/lsr/#PQR/202411210012/202411210012"}, "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-124.09, 46.69]}}, {"id": "22", "type": "Feature", "properties": {"valid": "2024-12-26T20:27:00Z", "type": "D", "magnitude": null, "city": "Dexter", "county": "Lane", "state": "OR", "source": "Public", "remark": "Damage: RV parking structure (metal, 12 x 15) flattened.", "wfo": "PQR", "typetext": "TSTM WND DMG", "lon0": -122.81, "lat0": 43.92, "events": "", "tdq": false, "warned": false, "leadtime": null, "lsrtype": "SV", "link": "https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/lsr/#PQR/202412262027/202412262027"}, "geometry": {"type": "Point", "coordinates": [-122.81, 43.92]}}]}}